This paper is primarily focused on load balancing in datacenter networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of software-defined networking (SDN) and control plane algorithms, which could fall under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of queueing theory and TCP traffic, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), information theory (cs.IT), and performance (cs.PF).
